Project Summary
===============
NextJS 15 Starter Template ‚Äî a minimal, production-ready foundation for building modern web applications. Pre-configured with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, and essential Next.js App Router patterns. Ships with a placeholder HomePage component ready to be replaced by the user's app.

Architecture Overview
====================
Single-page Next.js App Router app. Server Components by default; any interactivity lives in client components under `components/`. Top-level routing files (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `loading.tsx`) are all server components ‚Äî `'use client'` NEVER appears at this level (breaks WebContainer prerendering). Styling is Tailwind CSS 4 via `@import "tailwindcss";` in `app/globals.css`.

Key Components
==============

- **Page** (`app/page.tsx`) ‚Äî Server Component wrapper. Imports and renders `<HomePage />`. Must stay a Server Component (WebContainer breaks with 'use client' at this level).
- **HomePage** (`components/HomePage.tsx`) ‚Äî Placeholder component. This is the file Dex replaces with the user's actual app. Can be a client component ('use client').
- **RootLayout** (`app/layout.tsx`) ‚Äî Root HTML shell. Loads Geist Sans + Geist Mono via `next/font/google` and defines SEO metadata. Antialiasing enabled.
- **Error Boundary** (`app/error.tsx`) ‚Äî Runtime error recovery with retry.
- **NotFound** (`app/not-found.tsx`) ‚Äî 404 page. Plain server component using only `Link` from `next/link` and inline SVG.
- **Loading** (`app/loading.tsx`) ‚Äî Route transition spinner.

Agent Memory
============
- `.walden-memories/` ‚Äî shared folder where specialists write working documents for each other. Design specs, debug reports, SEO audits. Agents read from here instead of receiving large specs through Walden's token budget.

Invariants
==========
- `app/*/page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `error.tsx` are ALWAYS Server Components. No `'use client'`, no hooks, no event handlers at this layer.
- Client interactivity (useState, useEffect, onClick) lives in `components/*.tsx` with `'use client'`.
- No database. No env vars. No auth. No persistence ‚Äî any state is ephemeral.
- `.env.local` exists at project root but is managed by the app (not written by agents directly).

Notes for agents
================
- Dependencies, versions, and the directory tree are NOT duplicated here. Read `package.json` or `list_directory` for that.
- When you change the project structure, update THIS file accordingly: add new components under Key Components, document new invariants, update the Architecture Overview if the fundamental shape shifts.
